## Build Linkers

Development builds use `mold` on Linux through `.cargo/config.toml` so local
debug builds link quickly. Debug code generation uses Cranelift for faster
local checks. Coverage generation uses `lld` instead because the LLVM coverage
tools expect LLVM-compatible linker behaviour.

Install both linkers before running the full workflow locally:

```sh
sudo apt-get install clang lld mold
```

Run coverage with:

```sh
make coverage
```
